    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date>Tammuz 21st 5603</date>
            </p>
            <p>To <addressee>Abram Hart Esqr.</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The vestry &amp; members of the</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Congregation “Mikveh Israel” <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(3)"><sic>Bretheren</sic>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">In behalf of the Congrega-<lb/>tion Beth Elohim of this city, we
                earnestly appeal to you to<lb/> permit your Hazan the <persName>Revd Isaac
                    Leeser</persName> to come on to<lb/>
                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>, for the purpose of giving Testimony in a case
                about<lb/> to be tried, which involves questions not only of the<lb/> greatest
                importance to us, but of deep interest to the<lb/> whole House of
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName>. A party in our Congregation<lb/> have undertaken
                to sap the foundations of our sacred<lb/> Institutions, and to introduce
                innovations, which must<lb/> lead to the eventual overthrow of the Jewish Ritual
                as<lb/> established for age past. With this party unfortunately<lb/> has united our
                late Hazan the <persName>Revd. G. Poznanski</persName>, and<lb/> we are led to
                believe that he will be brought forward<lb/> as a witness to maintain these
                innovations and to endeavor<lb/> to prove them consistent with the Institutions of
                our<lb/> People. It will need therefore the learning and character<lb/> of some of
                our best-informed teachers to expose the errors<lb/> and inconsistencies of such
                innovations, and we know<lb/> no one whose learning and reputation could be
                more<lb/> certainly relied upon, than the Revd Hazan whom it is<lb/> your good
                fortune to have. We are struggling to maintain<lb/> the Institutions and Faith of
                our common ancestors against<lb/> an array of influence, which but for our Trust in
                that<lb/> Great Being who will always support the right might<lb/> deter us from our
                duty. But we are determined to stand<lb/> up to the last, and not permit Rationalism
                or Infidelity<lb/> to invade our Sanctuary. Fully confident that your<lb/>
                sympathies are with us, and that you will regard<lb/> us but as the outposts in
                fighting the Common Battle<lb/> of the Struse<add>?</add> of
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName>, and cannot doubt, that you<lb/> will consent to
                spare us your Hazan for a short time.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>The case in which we need the Testimony of your Hazan<lb/> is in such a form that our
                Lawyers advise us, will need his<lb/> personal presence, as no Testimony can be
                taken in writing.<lb/> The trial is expected to take place on the <date>8th of
                    August</date><lb/> and we only ask therefore, that you dispense with
                    <persName>Mr. Leeser</persName><lb/> for the space of a Fortnight, after which
                time we hope he<lb/> will return to you improved in health as our City is
                perfectly<lb/> healthy.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">With sincere prayers for the prosperity of your<lb/> Congregation.
                We remain your friends and<lb/> Brethren in <placeName>Israel</placeName> -</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName>Baich<add>?</add> Moses</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName>Sol Moses</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName>Isaac Woolf</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName>Abraham Johas<add>?</add></persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Attested</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName>S Valentine</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Secry &amp; Treasr.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">K. K. B. E.</p>
            <p rend="The following is written sideways to the right of the list of signatures"
                >Trustees of K. K. B. E.</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Mr. Abraham Hart</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">President of the Congregation “Mikveh Israel„</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <placeName>Pa</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="The following is written sideways to the left of the address">Letter &amp;
                Proceedings from the Congregation<lb/> K. K. B. E. <date>21st Tammus</date><lb/>
                Also copy of reply <date>July 25. 1843</date>.<lb/> (<date>1843</date>)</p>
